			<div class="wrap-content aos-init aos-animate" data-aos="fade-up">
				<p>Elastic Mint were approached by a well-known global company in early 2019 to develop a portal to showcase internal projects.</p>
<p>The idea was that senior people on project teams would enter information about the project, the team and milestones. Other users within the business would see a read-only view of the projects they were interested in. Administrators could configure which projects would be highlighted in a carousel component on the home page.</p>
<p>Initially, we worked closely with one of their graphics designers to produce a prototype. This ensured that we understood the vision and were able to accommodate any changes as it developed.</p>
<p>After developing the initial prototype, we continued our partnership for another three years, enhancing the portal and expanding it to cover projects across the global business.</p>
<p><strong>Technologies</strong>: ASP .Net Core, ASP .Net Razor Pages, SQL Server, Entity Framework Core, Azure</p>
